<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1780,2023]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1780,1806]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Body cylindrical. Pereonite 1 fused to head, with shallow transverse groove on former suture line. Lateral margins of head and pereonite 1 margin deep, convex, embracing mouthparts and pereopod 1 laterally. Pereonite 4 longest, 2–4 times as long as pereonite 3. All pleonites fused with pleotelson, with at least 2 pairs of lateral wings. Antenna with large spines on peduncle articles 2 and 3; flagellum short, with 3 articles and 1 distal claw-like article in females; in males distal article spine-like. Pereopod 1 dactylus short, without unguis. Pereopods 2–4 not flexed between carpus and propodus, with paired long setae along lower margin; with small claw-like dactyli, with short unguis. Pereopods 5–7 dactyli with 2 ungues. Male pleopod 1 simple, exopod without diagonal groove.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
